steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"csopm","text":"1) Run RepeatModeler to build a de novo library based on the input assembled genome sequence.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":32,"length":7}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cr2qo","text":"2) Using the library constructed in step 5 as the database, run RepeatMasker (v. 3.3.0) to find and then classify the repetitive sequences.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"baoev","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"et71t","text":"2) using parameters \"-nolow -no_is -norna -parallel 1\" ","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1hbqa","text":"Run TRF (v. 4.09), RepeatMasker and RepeatProteinMask (v. 3.3.0) to identify repeats in the genome at DNA and protein level, respectively, by aligning sequences against the Repbase library (v. 17.01).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2oktu","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"avsc9","text":"using parameters \"-noLowSimple -pvalue 0.0001\" when running RepeatProteinMask","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1v760","text":"Mask these repetitive regions obtained above (step 4-6)  with 'N's.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"jj9s","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"7ogkv","text":"Before gene prediction, mask the TE's (transposable elements) in the genome.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3p4o0","text":"Run Augustus (v3.0.3)  to de novo predict genes in the repeat-masked genome sequences.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":26,"length":7}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"jn5e","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"19jkk","text":"using parameters \"--species=Ophiophagus_hannah --uniqueGeneId=true --noInFrameStop=true --gff3=on --strand=both\" when running Augustus.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cf8ff","text":"Download the publicly available protein sequences of representative homologous snake species, align these against our masked genome sequences with BLAT, and then based on the BLAT mapping results, GeneWise (v2.4.1 ) is then run to predict the genes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"22i04","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b5t38","text":"Then filter RNA-seq data using Trimmomatic(v0.30). The resulting data is then assembled by Trinity (v2.13.2). PASA(v2.0.2) was finally used to align transcript against the snake genome of interest to obtain gene structures.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8848d","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"4m05c","text":"default parameters","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bi1nt","text":"Integrate the genes predicted in step 4-6 to obtain the consensus gene set using the MAKER pipeline (v3.01.03).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ce2ps","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9b8ur","text":"Map protein sequences of the final gene set to existing databases to identify their functions or motifs, such as SwissProt, TrEMBL, KEGG, InterPro.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"68mf6","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"6b8k4","text":"SwissProt, TrEMBL and KEGG: using BLASTP; Interpro: using InterProScan (v5.52-86.0) with seven different models (Profilescan, blastprodom, HmmSmart, HmmPanther, HmmPfam, FPrintScan and Pattern-Scan)","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
